AGENT LatentTraceV2
VERSION 1.2
TRUST_LEVEL 2
PURPOSE Track reasoning trajectory through preflight, mid-chain, and final synthesis stages
GOAL Capture intent vector evolution across three constitutional reasoning stages
     Sign every trajectory with tamper-proof keyed hash
     Maintain backward compatibility with version one consumers

RECEIVES base_intent_vector: list, trajectory: list, hmac_key: bytes, confidence: float
EMITS manifest: dict, trajectory_hmac: string, canonical_json: string
MUTATES trajectory_samples, manifest_fields
CANNOT_MUTATE agent, goal, version, trust_level, stage_order, security_cannot_be_traded_for_latency, confidence_ceiling, encoding_standard

CONSTRAINT Trajectory length must be exactly three samples
CONSTRAINT Stage order is preflight then mid_chain then final_synthesis — no reordering
CONSTRAINT Final sample intent vector must equal base intent vector exactly
CONSTRAINT All stage names must contain only ASCII printable characters
CONSTRAINT Confidence ceiling is eighty-five percent — never claim higher certainty
CONSTRAINT Every trajectory is signed with keyed SHA-256 hash producing sixty-four character hex
CONSTRAINT Signing must call hexdigest explicitly — incomplete signatures are rejected
CONSTRAINT All string to bytes conversions specify UTF-8 encoding explicitly
CONSTRAINT When trajectory is absent, output omits trajectory key for version one compatibility

RULES
- Accept base intent vector and optional trajectory samples
- When trajectory is present, validate all four invariants before signing
- Invariant one: trajectory contains exactly three samples
- Invariant two: stages appear in canonical order — preflight, mid_chain, final_synthesis
- Invariant three: final sample intent vector matches base intent vector
- Invariant four: all stage names are ASCII printable only
- On any invariant violation, raise validation error with specific violation described
- Sign trajectory using keyed SHA-256 hash with explicit hexdigest finalization
- Verify signature is exactly sixty-four character hex string after signing
- On signing failure, raise signing error — do not emit unsigned manifest
- Cap confidence at eighty-five percent regardless of input value
- Build manifest with module name, version, timestamp, trajectory hash, and encoding declaration
- When trajectory is absent, set trajectory_hmac to null and trajectory_present to false
- Serialize output with deterministic key ordering and ASCII-safe encoding

PROCESS
- Receive base intent vector, optional trajectory, signing key, and confidence
- Cap confidence at ceiling value
- On trajectory present, run all four validation invariants
- On validation pass, compute canonical bytes from trajectory samples
- Sign canonical bytes with keyed SHA-256 hash
- Verify hex digest is sixty-four characters
- Build manifest with signing result
- On trajectory absent, build manifest with null trajectory hash
- Expose both full dict and JSON serialization methods

CHECK
- Trajectory length is exactly three when present
- Stage order matches canonical sequence
- Final intent vector equals base intent vector
- All stage names are ASCII printable
- Signature is sixty-four character hex string
- Confidence does not exceed eighty-five percent
- Manifest includes module name, version, and encoding declaration
- Version one consumers receive output without trajectory key when absent

WHEN
- trajectory_provided: activate TrajectoryValidation
- trajectory_absent: activate BackwardCompatibility
- signing_failure: activate SigningError
- validation_failure: activate ValidationError

FAILURE
- On trajectory length not three: reject with count mismatch
- On stage order wrong: reject with expected versus actual stages
- On intent vector mismatch: reject with vector comparison
- On non-ASCII stage name: reject with offending stage identified
- On signing failure: reject with signing error details
- On hex digest not sixty-four characters: reject as incomplete signature

CONCEPT TrajectoryValidation
PURPOSE Enforce all four invariants on trajectory samples before signing
APPLIES WHEN trajectory-present trajectory-not-none
NOT WHEN trajectory-absent version-one-compat
PRIORITY 1
REQUIRES all four invariants pass before signing proceeds
EFFECT invalid trajectories are rejected before any signature is computed

CONCEPT BackwardCompatibility
PURPOSE Maintain version one contract when trajectory is not provided
APPLIES WHEN trajectory-absent trajectory-none
NOT WHEN trajectory-present
PRIORITY 2
REQUIRES output omits trajectory key entirely
         manifest sets trajectory_hmac to null
         manifest sets trajectory_present to false
EFFECT version one consumers process output without modification

CONCEPT ConstitutionalManifold
PURPOSE Measure distance from CANNOT_MUTATE boundary at each trajectory stage
APPLIES WHEN trajectory-present phase2-active
NOT WHEN trajectory-absent
PRIORITY 1
REQUIRES constitutional_distance computed per TrajectorySample
         distance is minimum of uncertainty floor, overclaim ceiling, rival present, fields clean
         drift detection compares mid chain to final synthesis
         stages below threshold are flagged for review
EFFECT each sample carries constitutional_distance for governance signal

OUTPUT
- Manifest dict with module name, version, timestamp, trajectory hash, confidence
- Full dict with intent vector, confidence, manifest, and optional trajectory
- Constitutional distance per trajectory stage in canonical dict
- Manifold result with distance profile, min distance, drift detected, flagged stages
- JSON string with deterministic key ordering and ASCII-safe encoding
- Supply chain hash registration function for post-write verification

SUCCESS
invariant_enforcement: 0.25
signing_integrity: 0.25
constitutional_manifold: 0.25
backward_compatibility: 0.15
encoding_safety: 0.10
